        {
            "title": "Industrial Atlas Copco's profit falls slightly less than expected, sees unchanged demand short-term",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>STOCKHOLM (Reuters) -Swedish industrial group Atlas Copco reported on Thursday a fall in third-quarter profit that was slightly smaller than expected and predicted customer activity would remain at the current level in the short term.</p><p>\n              Operating profit before items affecting comparability was 8.86 billion crowns ($941 million) against a year-earlier 9.44 billion on a 3% sales drop. Analysts polled by LSEG had on average forecast a profit of 8.68 billion crowns.</p><!-- Article --><p>\n              Order intake fell 4% to 40.5 billion crowns against a forecast 41.0 billion. Excluding acquisitions, the intake was however unchanged. </p><p>\n              The company said in a statement demand for its products and services had been mixed in the quarter, but that overall order volumes remained relatively stable compared both to last year and the second quarter.</p><p>\n              Atlas Copco, which last year generated roughly a quarter of group revenues in North America, said higher costs related to trade tariffs squeezed profit margins across its divisions.</p><p>\n              Shares in the company, which makes a wide range of industrial products from air treatment systems to construction equipment and power tools, were roughly unchanged at 1038 GMT. </p><p>\n               (Reporting by Jagoda Darlak in Gdansk and Greta Rosen Fondahn in Stockholm, editing by Anna Ringstrom)</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/industrial-atlas-copco-s-profit-falls-slightly-less-than-expected-sees-unchanged-demand-short-term-ce7d5dd8d88bfe2d",
            "pub_date": "2025-10-23 18:45:39",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
